      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that the \"official\" explanation is technical errors, but that feels like a really lazy way to ignore the sheer timing of it all. if we assume for a second that those \"errors\" were actually intentional silence to prevent the public from hearing what was really being discussed on the surface, how would someone even start to look for the truth? if the official archives are sanitized, are there any specific types of unclassified declassified documents or different agency databases—maybe military ones instead of just NASA—that might contain the raw, unedited data from that era? i'm looking for the stuff they didn't want us to see.",
